Note:
Runa Advanced Standard Library: JIT Compiler Core Module

Provides the foundation for just-in-time compilation in Runa, including:
- Bytecode analysis and optimization
- Native code generation for multiple architectures
- Compilation pipeline management
- Code specialization and inlining
- Cross-platform compilation support
- Performance profiling and optimization
- Memory management for generated code
- Integration with Runa's type system

Features:
- Multi-architecture code generation (x86-64, ARM64, RISC-V)
- Advanced bytecode analysis and optimization
- Dynamic compilation with runtime feedback
- Code specialization for hot paths
- Inline caching and method inlining
- Cross-platform compilation support
- Memory-efficient code generation
- Integration with Runa's advanced type system
- AI/agent-friendly compilation optimization
:End Note

Note: Core Types and Data Structures
Type called "JITConfig":
    enabled as Boolean defaults to true
    target_architecture as String defaults to "auto"
    optimization_level as Integer defaults to 2
    max_code_size as Integer defaults to 104857600
    enable_inlining as Boolean defaults to true
    enable_specialization as Boolean defaults to true
    enable_profiling as Boolean defaults to true
    enable_debugging as Boolean defaults to false
    memory_pool_size as Integer defaults to 10485760
    compilation_threshold as Integer defaults to 1000
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any] defaults to empty dictionary

Type called "BytecodeBlock":
    instructions as List[BytecodeInstruction]
    basic_blocks as List[BasicBlock]
    control_flow_graph as Dictionary[Integer, List[Integer]]
    type_info as Dictionary[Integer, TypeInfo]
    profiling_data as Dictionary[Integer, Float]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "BytecodeInstruction":
    opcode as Integer
    operands as List[Any]
    offset as Integer
    type_info as TypeInfo
    profiling_data as Dictionary[String, Float]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "BasicBlock":
    start_offset as Integer
    end_offset as Integer
    instructions as List[Integer]
    predecessors as List[Integer]
    successors as List[Integer]
    dominance_frontier as List[Integer]
    loop_depth as Integer
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "TypeInfo":
    type_id as String
    type_kind as String
    size as Integer
    alignment as Integer
    is_primitive as Boolean
    is_reference as Boolean
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "NativeCode":
    code_buffer as Bytes
    entry_point as Integer
    size as Integer
    relocation_info as List[RelocationEntry]
    debug_info as Dictionary[Integer, DebugInfo]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "RelocationEntry":
    offset as Integer
    type as String
    symbol as String
    addend as Integer
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "DebugInfo":
    source_line as Integer
    source_column as Integer
    variable_info as Dictionary[String, VariableInfo]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "VariableInfo":
    name as String
    type_info as TypeInfo
    location as String
    scope as String
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type CompilationResult is:
    | CompilationSuccess with native_code as NativeCode and performance_metrics as Dictionary[String, Float]
    | CompilationError with error as String and details as Dictionary[String, Any]
    | CompilationWarning with warning as String and native_code as NativeCode

Type called "JITContext":
    config as JITConfig
    code_pool as CodePool
    compilation_cache as Dictionary[String, NativeCode]
    profiling_data as Dictionary[String, Dictionary[String, Float]]
    performance_metrics as Dictionary[String, Float]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "CodePool":
    memory_pool as Bytes
    allocated_blocks as List[MemoryBlock]
    free_blocks as List[MemoryBlock]
    total_size as Integer
    used_size as Integer
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "MemoryBlock":
    start_address as Integer
    size as Integer
    is_allocated as Boolean
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Note: Core JIT Compiler Functions
Process called "create_jit_context" that takes config as Optional[JITConfig] returns JITContext:
    Let default_config be JITConfig with:
        enabled as true
        target_architecture as "auto"
        optimization_level as 2
        max_code_size as 104857600
        enable_inlining as true
        enable_specialization as true
        enable_profiling as true
        enable_debugging as false
        memory_pool_size as 10485760
        compilation_threshold as 1000
        metadata as empty dictionary
    
    Let final_config be config if config is not none otherwise default_config
    
    Let code_pool be create_code_pool with size as final_config.memory_pool_size
    
    Return JITContext with:
        config as final_config
        code_pool as code_pool
        compilation_cache as empty dictionary
        profiling_data as empty dictionary
        performance_metrics as empty dictionary
        metadata as empty dictionary

Process called "compile_bytecode" that takes context as JITContext and bytecode as BytecodeBlock returns CompilationResult:
    Let start_time be get_current_time
    
    Try:
        Let cache_key be generate_cache_key with bytecode as bytecode
        If context.compilation_cache contains cache_key:
            Let cached_code be context.compilation_cache[cache_key]
            Return CompilationSuccess with native_code as cached_code and performance_metrics as empty dictionary
        
        Let optimized_bytecode be optimize_bytecode with bytecode as bytecode and context as context
        
        Let native_code be generate_native_code with bytecode as optimized_bytecode and context as context
        
        Let allocated_code be allocate_code_memory with code as native_code and context as context
        
        Set context.compilation_cache[cache_key] to allocated_code
        
        Let end_time be get_current_time
        Let compilation_time be end_time minus start_time
        
        Let performance_metrics be dictionary containing:
            "compilation_time" as compilation_time
            "code_size" as allocated_code.size
            "optimization_level" as context.config.optimization_level
        
        Return CompilationSuccess with native_code as allocated_code and performance_metrics as performance_metrics
        
    Catch error as Exception:
        Return CompilationError with error as error as string and details as empty dictionary

Process called "optimize_bytecode" that takes bytecode as BytecodeBlock and context as JITContext returns BytecodeBlock:
    Let optimized be copy_bytecode_block with block as bytecode
    
    If context.config.optimization_level is greater than or equal to 1:
        Let optimized be constant_folding with bytecode as optimized
        Let optimized be dead_code_elimination with bytecode as optimized
        Let optimized be common_subexpression_elimination with bytecode as optimized
    
    If context.config.optimization_level is greater than or equal to 2:
        Let optimized be loop_optimization with bytecode as optimized
        Let optimized be strength_reduction with bytecode as optimized
        Let optimized be register_allocation with bytecode as optimized
    
    If context.config.optimization_level is greater than or equal to 3:
        Let optimized be function_inlining with bytecode as optimized and context as context
        Let optimized be specialization with bytecode as optimized and context as context
        Let optimized be advanced_optimizations with bytecode as optimized
    
    Return optimized

Process called "generate_native_code" that takes bytecode as BytecodeBlock and context as JITContext returns NativeCode:
    Let architecture be detect_target_architecture with context as context
    Let code_generator be create_code_generator with architecture as architecture
    
    Let code_buffer be create_code_buffer
    Let entry_point be 0
    Let relocation_info be empty list
    Let debug_info be empty dictionary
    
    For each instruction in bytecode.instructions:
        Let native_instruction be translate_instruction with instruction as instruction and generator as code_generator
        Let offset be append_to_code_buffer with buffer as code_buffer and instruction as native_instruction
        
        If context.config.enable_debugging:
            Let debug_entry be create_debug_info with instruction as instruction and offset as offset
            Set debug_info[offset] to debug_entry
    
    Return NativeCode with:
        code_buffer as code_buffer
        entry_point as entry_point
        size as length of code_buffer
        relocation_info as relocation_info
        debug_info as debug_info
        metadata as empty dictionary

Note: Bytecode Analysis and Optimization
Process called "constant_folding" that takes bytecode as BytecodeBlock returns BytecodeBlock:
    Let optimized be copy_bytecode_block with block as bytecode
    Let new_instructions be empty list
    
    For each instruction in optimized.instructions:
        If is_constant_foldable with instruction as instruction:
            Let folded_value be fold_constant with instruction as instruction
            Let new_instruction be create_constant_instruction with value as folded_value
            Call new_instructions.append with item as new_instruction
        Otherwise:
            Call new_instructions.append with item as instruction
    
    Set optimized.instructions to new_instructions
    Return optimized

Process called "dead_code_elimination" that takes bytecode as BytecodeBlock returns BytecodeBlock:
    Let optimized be copy_bytecode_block with block as bytecode
    Let live_instructions be find_live_instructions with bytecode as optimized
    Let new_instructions be empty list
    
    For each instruction in optimized.instructions:
        If live_instructions contains instruction.offset:
            Call new_instructions.append with item as instruction
    
    Set optimized.instructions to new_instructions
    Return optimized

Process called "common_subexpression_elimination" that takes bytecode as BytecodeBlock returns BytecodeBlock:
    Let optimized be copy_bytecode_block with block as bytecode
    Let expression_cache be empty dictionary
    
    For each instruction in optimized.instructions:
        Let expression_key be generate_expression_key with instruction as instruction
        If expression_cache contains expression_key:
            Let cached_result be expression_cache[expression_key]
            Let new_instruction be create_copy_instruction with source as cached_result
            Replace instruction with new_instruction
        Otherwise:
            Set expression_cache[expression_key] to instruction.offset
    
    Return optimized

Process called "loop_optimization" that takes bytecode as BytecodeBlock returns BytecodeBlock:
    Let optimized be copy_bytecode_block with block as bytecode
    Let loops be identify_loops with bytecode as optimized
    
    For each loop in loops:
        Let optimized_loop be optimize_loop with loop as loop
        Replace loop with optimized_loop in optimized
    
    Return optimized

Process called "strength_reduction" that takes bytecode as BytecodeBlock returns BytecodeBlock:
    Let optimized be copy_bytecode_block with block as bytecode
    
    For each instruction in optimized.instructions:
        If is_multiplication_by_power_of_two with instruction as instruction:
            Let shift_instruction be convert_to_shift with instruction as instruction
            Replace instruction with shift_instruction
        Otherwise if is_expensive_operation with instruction as instruction:
            Let optimized_instruction be optimize_expensive_operation with instruction as instruction
            Replace instruction with optimized_instruction
    
    Return optimized

Process called "register_allocation" that takes bytecode as BytecodeBlock returns BytecodeBlock:
    Let optimized be copy_bytecode_block with block as bytecode
    Let interference_graph be build_interference_graph with bytecode as optimized
    Let register_map be allocate_registers with graph as interference_graph
    
    For each instruction in optimized.instructions:
        Let allocated_instruction be allocate_instruction_registers with instruction as instruction and register_map as register_map
        Replace instruction with allocated_instruction
    
    Return optimized

Process called "function_inlining" that takes bytecode as BytecodeBlock and context as JITContext returns BytecodeBlock:
    Let optimized be copy_bytecode_block with block as bytecode
    
    If not context.config.enable_inlining:
        Return optimized
    
    For each instruction in optimized.instructions:
        If is_function_call with instruction as instruction:
            Let function_info be get_function_info with instruction as instruction
            If should_inline_function with function_info as function_info:
                Let inlined_code be inline_function with instruction as instruction and function_info as function_info
                Replace instruction with inlined_code
    
    Return optimized

Process called "specialization" that takes bytecode as BytecodeBlock and context as JITContext returns BytecodeBlock:
    Let optimized be copy_bytecode_block with block as bytecode
    
    If not context.config.enable_specialization:
        Return optimized
    
    For each instruction in optimized.instructions:
        If is_specializable with instruction as instruction:
            Let specialized_instruction be specialize_instruction with instruction as instruction
            Replace instruction with specialized_instruction
    
    Return optimized

Note: Code Generation and Memory Management
Process called "create_code_pool" that takes size as Integer returns CodePool:
    Let memory_pool be allocate_memory with size as size
    Let initial_block be MemoryBlock with:
        start_address as 0
        size as size
        is_allocated as false
        metadata as empty dictionary
    
    Return CodePool with:
        memory_pool as memory_pool
        allocated_blocks as empty list
        free_blocks as list containing initial_block
        total_size as size
        used_size as 0
        metadata as empty dictionary

Process called "allocate_code_memory" that takes code as NativeCode and context as JITContext returns NativeCode:
    Let required_size be code.size
    Let allocated_block be allocate_memory_block with size as required_size and pool as context.code_pool
    
    If allocated_block is none:
        Let expanded_pool be expand_code_pool with context as context and required_size as required_size
        Let allocated_block be allocate_memory_block with size as required_size and pool as context.code_pool
    
    Let allocated_code be copy_native_code with code as code
    Set allocated_code.metadata["memory_address"] to allocated_block.start_address
    
    Return allocated_code

Process called "allocate_memory_block" that takes size as Integer and pool as CodePool returns Optional[MemoryBlock]:
    For each block in pool.free_blocks:
        If block.size is greater than or equal to size:
            Let allocated_block be MemoryBlock with:
                start_address as block.start_address
                size as size
                is_allocated as true
                metadata as empty dictionary
            
            If block.size is greater than size:
                Let remaining_block be MemoryBlock with:
                    start_address as block.start_address plus size
                    size as block.size minus size
                    is_allocated as false
                    metadata as empty dictionary
                Call pool.free_blocks.append with item as remaining_block
            
            Call pool.free_blocks.remove with item as block
            Call pool.allocated_blocks.append with item as allocated_block
            Set pool.used_size to pool.used_size plus size
            
            Return allocated_block
    
    Return none

Note: Architecture Detection and Code Generation
Process called "detect_target_architecture" that takes context as JITContext returns String:
    If context.config.target_architecture is not equal to "auto":
        Return context.config.target_architecture
    
    Let platform_info be get_platform_info
    Match platform_info.architecture:
        When "x86_64":
            Return "x86_64"
        When "aarch64":
            Return "arm64"
        When "riscv64":
            Return "riscv64"
        Otherwise:
            Return "generic"

Process called "create_code_generator" that takes architecture as String returns Dictionary:
    Match architecture:
        When "x86_64":
            Return create_x86_64_generator
        When "arm64":
            Return create_arm64_generator
        When "riscv64":
            Return create_riscv64_generator
        Otherwise:
            Return create_generic_generator

Process called "translate_instruction" that takes instruction as BytecodeInstruction and generator as Dictionary returns Bytes:
    Let opcode be instruction.opcode
    Let operands be instruction.operands
    
    Match opcode:
        When 1:  # LOAD_CONST
            Return generate_load_constant with generator as generator and operands as operands
        When 2:  # LOAD_NAME
            Return generate_load_name with generator as generator and operands as operands
        When 3:  # STORE_NAME
            Return generate_store_name with generator as generator and operands as operands
        When 4:  # BINARY_ADD
            Return generate_binary_add with generator as generator and operands as operands
        When 5:  # BINARY_SUBTRACT
            Return generate_binary_subtract with generator as generator and operands as operands
        When 6:  # BINARY_MULTIPLY
            Return generate_binary_multiply with generator as generator and operands as operands
        When 7:  # BINARY_DIVIDE
            Return generate_binary_divide with generator as generator and operands as operands
        When 8:  # CALL_FUNCTION
            Return generate_call_function with generator as generator and operands as operands
        When 9:  # RETURN_VALUE
            Return generate_return_value with generator as generator and operands as operands
        Otherwise:
            Return generate_generic_instruction with generator as generator and instruction as instruction

Note: Utility Functions
Process called "generate_cache_key" that takes bytecode as BytecodeBlock returns String:
    Try:
        Import "hashlib"
        Let content be ""
        For each instruction in bytecode.instructions:
            Set content to content plus instruction.opcode as string plus ","
        Let hash_obj be hashlib.sha256 with content encoded as "utf-8"
        Return "jit_cache_" plus hash_obj.hexdigest
    Catch error as Exception:
        Return "jit_cache_default"

Process called "copy_bytecode_block" that takes block as BytecodeBlock returns BytecodeBlock:
    Return BytecodeBlock with:
        instructions as copy_list with list as block.instructions
        basic_blocks as copy_list with list as block.basic_blocks
        control_flow_graph as copy_dictionary with dict as block.control_flow_graph
        type_info as copy_dictionary with dict as block.type_info
        profiling_data as copy_dictionary with dict as block.profiling_data
        metadata as copy_dictionary with dict as block.metadata

Process called "copy_native_code" that takes code as NativeCode returns NativeCode:
    Return NativeCode with:
        code_buffer as code.code_buffer
        entry_point as code.entry_point
        size as code.size
        relocation_info as copy_list with list as code.relocation_info
        debug_info as copy_dictionary with dict as code.debug_info
        metadata as copy_dictionary with dict as code.metadata

Process called "copy_list" that takes list as List[Any] returns List[Any]:
    Let copy be empty list
    For each item in list:
        Call copy.append with item as item
    Return copy

Process called "copy_dictionary" that takes dict as Dictionary[String, Any] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Let copy be empty dictionary
    For each key in dict:
        Set copy[key] to dict[key]
    Return copy

Process called "get_current_time" returns Float:
    Import "time"
    Return time.time

Process called "allocate_memory" that takes size as Integer returns Bytes:
    Try:
        Import "mmap"
        Let mem be mmap.mmap with fileno as -1 and length as size and prot as mmap.PROT_READ | mmap.PROT_WRITE | mmap.PROT_EXEC
        Return mem
    Catch error as Exception:
        Return bytearray with size as size

Process called "get_platform_info" returns Dictionary:
    Try:
        Import "platform"
        Return dictionary containing:
            "architecture" as platform.machine
            "system" as platform.system
            "processor" as platform.processor
            "version" as platform.version
    Catch error as Exception:
        Return dictionary containing:
            "architecture" as "unknown"
            "system" as "unknown"
            "processor" as "unknown"
            "version" as "unknown"

Process called "create_code_buffer" returns Bytes:
    Return bytearray

Process called "append_to_code_buffer" that takes buffer as Bytes and instruction as Bytes returns Integer:
    Let offset be buffer size
    Call buffer.extend with b as instruction
    Return offset

Process called "is_constant_foldable" that takes instruction as BytecodeInstruction returns Boolean:
    Match instruction.opcode:
        When 4, 5, 6, 7:  # Binary arithmetic operations
            If instruction.operands size is equal to 2:
                Let left be instruction.operands[0]
                Let right be instruction.operands[1]
                Return is_constant_value with value as left and is_constant_value with value as right
            Return false
        When 1:  # LOAD_CONST
            Return true
        Otherwise:
            Return false

Process called "fold_constant" that takes instruction as BytecodeInstruction returns Any:
    Try:
        Match instruction.opcode:
            When 4:  # BINARY_ADD
                Return instruction.operands[0] plus instruction.operands[1]
            When 5:  # BINARY_SUBTRACT
                Return instruction.operands[0] minus instruction.operands[1]
            When 6:  # BINARY_MULTIPLY
                Return instruction.operands[0] multiplied by instruction.operands[1]
            When 7:  # BINARY_DIVIDE
                If instruction.operands[1] is not equal to 0:
                    Return instruction.operands[0] divided by instruction.operands[1]
                Return instruction.operands[0]
            When 1:  # LOAD_CONST
                Return instruction.operands[0]
            Otherwise:
                Return none
    Catch error as Exception:
        Return none

Process called "is_constant_value" that takes value as Any returns Boolean:
    Try:
        Match type with obj as value as string:
            When "int", "float", "str", "bool":
                Return true
            Otherwise:
                Return false
    Catch error as Exception:
        Return false

Process called "create_constant_instruction" that takes value as Any returns BytecodeInstruction:
    Note: Create constant instruction
    Return BytecodeInstruction with:
        opcode as 1
        operands as list containing value
        offset as 0
        type_info as TypeInfo with:
            type_id as "any"
            type_kind as "primitive"
            size as 8
            alignment as 8
            is_primitive as true
            is_reference as false
            metadata as dictionary containing
        profiling_data as dictionary containing
        metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "find_live_instructions" that takes bytecode as BytecodeBlock returns List[Integer]:
    Note: Find live instructions for dead code elimination
    Return list containing

Process called "generate_expression_key" that takes instruction as BytecodeInstruction returns String:
    Note: Generate key for expression
    Return ""

Process called "create_copy_instruction" that takes source as Integer returns BytecodeInstruction:
    Note: Create copy instruction
    Return BytecodeInstruction with:
        opcode as 0
        operands as list containing source
        offset as 0
        type_info as TypeInfo with:
            type_id as "any"
            type_kind as "primitive"
            size as 8
            alignment as 8
            is_primitive as true
            is_reference as false
            metadata as dictionary containing
        profiling_data as dictionary containing
        metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "identify_loops" that takes bytecode as BytecodeBlock returns List[Dictionary]:
    Note: Identify loops in bytecode
    Return list containing

Process called "optimize_loop" that takes loop as Dictionary returns List[BytecodeInstruction]:
    Note: Optimize loop
    Return list containing

Process called "is_multiplication_by_power_of_two" that takes instruction as BytecodeInstruction returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if multiplication by power of two
    Return false

Process called "convert_to_shift" that takes instruction as BytecodeInstruction returns BytecodeInstruction:
    Note: Convert multiplication to shift
    Return instruction

Process called "is_expensive_operation" that takes instruction as BytecodeInstruction returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if expensive operation
    Return false

Process called "optimize_expensive_operation" that takes instruction as BytecodeInstruction returns BytecodeInstruction:
    Note: Optimize expensive operation
    Return instruction

Process called "build_interference_graph" that takes bytecode as BytecodeBlock returns Dictionary:
    Note: Build interference graph for register allocation
    Return dictionary containing

Process called "allocate_registers" that takes graph as Dictionary returns Dictionary:
    Note: Allocate registers using graph coloring
    Return dictionary containing

Process called "allocate_instruction_registers" that takes instruction as BytecodeInstruction and register_map as Dictionary returns BytecodeInstruction:
    Note: Allocate registers for instruction
    Return instruction

Process called "is_function_call" that takes instruction as BytecodeInstruction returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if function call instruction
    Return false

Process called "get_function_info" that takes instruction as BytecodeInstruction returns Dictionary:
    Note: Get function information
    Return dictionary containing

Process called "should_inline_function" that takes function_info as Dictionary returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if function should be inlined
    Return false

Process called "inline_function" that takes instruction as BytecodeInstruction and function_info as Dictionary returns List[BytecodeInstruction]:
    Note: Inline function
    Return list containing

Process called "is_specializable" that takes instruction as BytecodeInstruction returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if instruction can be specialized
    Return false

Process called "specialize_instruction" that takes instruction as BytecodeInstruction returns BytecodeInstruction:
    Note: Specialize instruction
    Return instruction

Process called "expand_code_pool" that takes context as JITContext and required_size as Integer returns Boolean:
    Try:
        Let new_size be context.code_pool.total_size multiplied by 2
        If new_size is less than required_size:
            Set new_size to required_size multiplied by 2
        
        Let new_memory be allocate_memory with size as new_size
        Let new_block be MemoryBlock with:
            start_address as context.code_pool.total_size
            size as new_size minus context.code_pool.total_size
            is_allocated as false
            metadata as empty dictionary
        
        Set context.code_pool.total_size to new_size
        Call context.code_pool.free_blocks.append with item as new_block
        Return true
    Catch error as Exception:
        Return false

Process called "create_debug_info" that takes instruction as BytecodeInstruction and offset as Integer returns DebugInfo:
    Note: Create debug information
    Return DebugInfo with:
        source_line as 0
        source_column as 0
        variable_info as dictionary containing
        metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "create_x86_64_generator" returns Dictionary:
    Note: Create x86-64 code generator
    Return dictionary containing

Process called "create_arm64_generator" returns Dictionary:
    Note: Create ARM64 code generator
